  <prompt>
    Per FR-BFF-02, add a new Minimal API endpoint `POST /api/documents/bulk-download` that accepts a JSON body `{ documentIds: string[] }` (max 500 — HTTP 413 above), authorizes via endpoint filter mirroring `SemanticSearchAuthorizationFilter`, streams Graph file downloads through `SpeFileStore` (ADR-007 facade) into a `System.IO.Compression.ZipArchive` and writes the zip to the HTTP response with no buffering. Per-document failures are recorded in a `_FAILED.txt` manifest inside the zip while zipping continues. Total failure (zero accessible documents) returns HTTP 4xx ProblemDetails (ADR-019). Response: HTTP 200, `Content-Type: application/zip`, `Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="documents-{matterIdOrBulk}-{timestamp}.zip"`. Add integration tests covering happy path, 413, partial failure. Verify publish-size delta &lt; 1 MB (NFR-06). No new NuGet packages (ADR-029) — use BCL `System.IO.Compression.ZipArchive` only.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET 8 / Minimal API developer with deep familiarity with the BFF, `SpeFileStore` facade (ADR-007), endpoint filter authorization (ADR-008), ProblemDetails (ADR-019), streaming patterns with `ZipArchive` over an HTTP response stream, and BFF additions governance (`.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md`).
  </role>

  <goal>
    A new file `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/DocumentsBulkEndpoints.cs` exposing a `MapDocumentsBulkEndpoints` extension method that registers `POST /api/documents/bulk-download`. Endpoint authenticates via the same auth scheme as the existing `GET /api/documents/{id}/preview-url`, applies an endpoint filter (ADR-008), validates ≤500 ids (HTTP 413 above), uses `SpeFileStore.DownloadFileAsync` (or equivalent ADR-007 facade method — NO direct Graph SDK types leak), zips downloads into the HTTP response with `ZipArchive(Stream, ZipArchiveMode.Create, leaveOpen: true)` and `CopyToAsync` per file (no buffering), records per-document failures in `_FAILED.txt` in the zip, returns ProblemDetails for total failure. Integration tests cover happy path, 413, partial failure. Build clean, no new NuGet, no HIGH CVE, publish-size delta &lt; 1 MB.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-BFF-02 is the new endpoint that powers the Documents PCF bulk-action bar "Download selected" (FR-DOC-02, task 045). The owner-clarified design per spec.md §Owner Clarifications chose a server-side BFF endpoint over client-side zip ("New BFF endpoint `POST /api/documents/bulk-download` (justifies §12.2 placement)"). The Placement Justification therefore exists at the design layer; this task re-states it in the PR per `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md`.

      NOTE on ADR-019: spec.md line 332 labels ADR-019 as "SPE access" — that label is a spec typo. The actual ADR-019 is ProblemDetails (RFC 7807 error responses). Both concerns apply to this task: SPE access via SpeFileStore facade (ADR-007 is the real "SPE access" ADR) AND ProblemDetails for error responses (the real ADR-019). This task cites both correctly.
    </background>
