  <steps>
    <step order="0">Step 0.5: This task does NOT touch Fluent v9 React components — `fluent-v9-component` skill is NOT applicable. Skip.</step>
    <step order="1">Load knowledge: `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` (binding pre-merge checklist), ADR-007/008/010/019/029, `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md`. Run the pre-merge checklist in §A in your head as you design.</step>
    <step order="2">Locate the SpeFileStore facade (Glob for `SpeFileStore*.cs`) and identify the download method (likely `DownloadFileAsync(driveId, itemId, ...)` returning a Stream). Confirm no Graph SDK types leak above the facade.</step>
    <step order="3">Locate `SemanticSearchAuthorizationFilter` (Glob `*AuthorizationFilter.cs` or `Api/Filters/`) — model the new endpoint filter on it. Decide whether to create a new `DocumentsBulkDownloadAuthorizationFilter` or reuse an existing document-scoped filter. Authorization scope mirrors `GET /api/documents/{id}/preview-url`.</step>
    <step order="4">Create `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/DocumentsBulkEndpoints.cs` with: (a) `MapDocumentsBulkEndpoints` extension method on `IEndpointRouteBuilder`; (b) `MapPost("/api/documents/bulk-download", Handle)` with `.AddEndpointFilter<...>()`, `.RequireAuthorization()`, `.RequireRateLimiting(...)` (use an existing policy from `api.md`, e.g., `"standard"` if one exists); (c) handler signature accepting the request DTO + HttpContext + SpeFileStore (and any required services via DI).</step>
    <step order="5">Implement the handler: (a) validate `documentIds.Length &gt; 500` → return `Results.Problem(statusCode: 413, ...)`; (b) resolve each documentId to (driveId, itemId, fileName) via existing Dataverse/SPE lookup (use the same service used by preview-url); (c) start writing to `HttpContext.Response.Body` with `Content-Type: application/zip` headers + `Content-Disposition` set; (d) wrap response body in `ZipArchive(stream, ZipArchiveMode.Create, leaveOpen: true)`; (e) for each documentId, attempt `SpeFileStore.DownloadFileAsync(...)`, create a `ZipArchiveEntry`, `CopyToAsync` the file stream into the entry stream — on per-document exception, capture (documentId, fileName, exception.Message) into a local `failedItems` list and continue; (f) after the loop, if `failedItems.Any()`, write `_FAILED.txt` entry with the manifest; (g) if `failedItems.Count == documentIds.Length` (zero successful), return `Results.Problem(statusCode: 502 or 4xx, ...)` instead of completing the zip — but note the response headers may already be flushed, so structure the handler to detect total failure BEFORE writing any zip bytes (i.e., pre-resolve all documentId → (driveId, itemId, fileName) and bail with ProblemDetails if all lookups fail).</step>
    <step order="6">Register `MapDocumentsBulkEndpoints` in `Program.cs` via the existing pattern (find `MapSemanticSearchEndpoints` to see where extension `.Map*Endpoints()` calls live).</step>
    <step order="7">Verify ADR-010: confirm no new DI registrations were added (reuse SpeFileStore, reuse Dataverse document lookup service). If you added any, push back and revisit.</step>
    <step order="8">Add integration tests in the existing Sprk.Bff.Api test project using `WebApplicationFactory`:
      <substeps>
        <substep>Happy path: POST with 3 valid documentIds; assert HTTP 200, application/zip, valid zip content, all 3 entries present, no _FAILED.txt.</substep>
        <substep>413: POST with 501 documentIds; assert HTTP 413 + ProblemDetails body.</substep>
        <substep>Partial failure: POST with 3 ids where 1 is unauthorized/not-found; assert HTTP 200, 2 valid entries + _FAILED.txt listing the failed one.</substep>
        <substep>Total failure: POST with 3 ids that all fail lookup; assert HTTP 4xx + ProblemDetails (no zip body).</substep>
      </substeps>
    </step>
    <step order="9">Build verification: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` clean; run all new integration tests; `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` shows no new HIGH CVE (no packages added — should be unchanged).</step>
    <step order="10">Verify publish-size impact (NFR-06): `dotnet publish src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ --runtime linux-x64 -c Release`. Compare output size before/after this task. Delta MUST be &lt; 1 MB. If delta exceeds, investigate (System.IO.Compression should be in the BCL with zero size delta).</step>
    <step order="11">Document the Placement Justification in the PR description per `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` §A.1: "Bulk download is latency-sensitive (user-facing action), requires same auth scheme + Dataverse + SPE access as existing single-file download endpoints, streams through BFF-managed Graph credentials and authorization — belongs in BFF. Uses BCL ZipArchive only, no new NuGet packages, no DI additions. Owner-clarified at design layer (spec.md §Owner Clarifications: 'New BFF endpoint... justifies §12.2 placement')."</step>
    <step order="12">Step 9.5 (FULL rigor): run `Skill code-review` + `Skill adr-check` — fix issues before completing.</step>
    <step order="13">Update TASK-INDEX.md: 051 → ✅. Update current-task.md to next pending task.</step>
  </steps>

